"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1932494-olympics-2024-silver-medallist-wins-appeal\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Faith Kipyegon's silver medal from the 5,000m final in Paris has been reinstated after the Kenyan runner was initially disqualified.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}, {\"begin\": 57, \"end\": 62, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999982427653, \"rank\": 1.7572239568129496e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kipyegon narrowly missed out on gold, having finished behind compatriot Beatrice Chebet in the final few metres of the race.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 208, \"end\": 223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beatrice Chebet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chebet was too strong for her countrywoman in the final straight, with the Kenyan kicking home to top the podium inside a time of 15 minutes.\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But following the race's conclusion, Kipyegon - who thought she'd done enough for at least a silver medal - learned her fate had already been decided.\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Adjudged to have obstructed the track two laps from the end, Kipyegon was disqualified by the race referees, with third-placed Sifan Hassan moved up to silver and Italy's Nadia Battocletti the new bronze medalist.\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 684, \"end\": 696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}, {\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9995205209501039, \"rank\": 0.00047631167157144216, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gudaf Tsegay was the woman at the heart of it all, with Kipyegon said to have jostled with the Ethiopian, who eventually finished the race in ninth.\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 772, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gudaf Tsegay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9339715795689831, \"rank\": 0.0706962874044263, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the drama did not stop there.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unsurprisingly, Kipyegon and Athletics Kenya were quick to lodge an appeal, which they discovered had been successful long after the race finished.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athletics Kenya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It meant Kenya took home a one-two finish in the women's 5,000-metre race, with Chebet's gold the first for the athletics-loving nation on the track at this year's Games.\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999992974153, \"rank\": 6.50335823996084e-10, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Official women's 5000m Podium finish.????????????\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beatrice Chebet ?\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beatrice Chebet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"?????????????????\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Faith Kipyegon ?\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1362, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"?????????????????\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sifan Hassan ?\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"??????????\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"?#Paris2024#OlympicGamesParis2024pic.twitter.com/7keSfxTsao    Speaking after the race, bronze medalist and Hassan revealed she was pleased Kipyegon had been reinstated, even if it denied the Dutch runner a silver medal.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.998366049844253, \"rank\": 0.0016239548373960077, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 31-year-old said: \\\"I am really happy Faith was reinstated.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's a phenomenal athlete and I have a lot of respect for her.\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would have been proud even if I was fourth.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an incredible field, and I love my bronze medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's unlikely to be much consolation for reigning European champion Battocletti, who just missed out on the podium, despite setting an Italian record on the Parisian track.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1925, \"end\": 1942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"score\": 0.999999791885806, \"rank\": 2.0806361357842202e-07, \"text\": \"Europ